content.text:
I've successfully implemented the fix for the issue. Here's a summary of the changes made:

## Summary of Changes

### 1. `ktlint-ruleset-standard/src/main/kotlin/com/pinterest/ktlint/ruleset/standard/rules/MultiLineIfElseRule.kt`

**Root Cause**: The check for `else if` constructs was nested inside a condition that required no newline before the `else` keyword (`!node.treePrev.textContains('\n')`). In multiline code, there IS a newline before the `else` keyword, so the `else if` check was never reached.

**Fix**: Moved the `else if` check outside of the newline condition so that `else if` constructs are allowed regardless of formatting:

```kotlin
// Before (buggy):
if (!node.treePrev.textContains('\n')) {
    if (node.firstChildNode.elementType == IF) {
        return  // Only reached when no newline before else
    }
    ...
}

// After (fixed):
if (node.firstChildNode?.elementType == IF) {
    // Allow "else if" construct both single-line and multi-line:
    // else if (...)
    return
}

if (!node.treePrev.textContains('\n')) {
    ...
}
```

### 2. `ktlint-ruleset-standard/src/test/kotlin/com/pinterest/ktlint/ruleset/standard/rules/MultiLineIfElseRuleTest.kt`

Added two test cases that verify the fix:
- Test case for the original issue example with `?: 0` suffix
- Test case for the additional example with `.plus("foo")` suffix

Both tests verify that properly-braced `else if` constructs are not incorrectly flagged as needing additional braces.

### 3. `CHANGELOG.md`

Added an entry in the "Fixed" section documenting the bug fix:
```
* Fix false positive for `else if` constructs in multiline if-else statements `multiline-if-else` ([#1904](https://github.com/pinterest/ktlint/issues/1904))
```

